            <thetext>The &quot;generate.py&quot; stub which is included in every skeleton should be able to use another configuration file besides the &quot;config.json&quot;.

At the moment the stub is looking for the &quot;config.json&quot; to determine a QOOXDOO_PATH. Even if the stub is called with the &quot;-c&quot; parameter to use another configuration file. 

If the stub is processing the &quot;-c&quot; parameter one is able to use a different QOOXDOO_PATH defined through a second configuration file. This is especially interesting for setups when generating the qooxdoo application with a build system like Hudson where the paths *can* be different than the setup of the developer.</thetext>
